{
  "texts": [
    "The field voltage affects the electromotive force (EMF) of the generator, which is directly factored in the electrical power output, P e,i of the generator via the network.",
    "This interconnection of the variables couples the electrical and mechanical behavior of the machine.",
    "It is represented through a simplified model given by:T A,i Ėfd,i = -E f d,i + K A,i (V ref,i -V i)(3)where T A,i is the time constant of the automatic voltage regulator (AVR), K A,i is the AVR gain, V ref,i is the voltage reference, and V i is the terminal voltage magnitude of the generator.",
    "b: Turbine-Governor SystemA turbine governor is used to control the input mechanical power according to primary frequency control, which essentially bridges the mechanical dynamics to the frequency dynamics of the power system.",
    "The model for the turbinegovernor system represents this relationship between mechanical power P m,i in response to frequency deviations."
  ]
}